						<summary>

						<p>This damaged record belongs to the reign of the Āḷupa king <hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍyachakravarti Kulaśēkharadēva</hi> and is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Manmatha, Makara, 18, Sōmavāra</hi> corresponding probably to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1176 January 12 Monday.</hi> It seems to record a gift made by <hi rend="bold">Chaṇḍabbe</hi> to the temple of the god Nakharēśvara at <hi rend="bold">Basaṟūru.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
